title: For Sale:  why do people not respond?
postcontent:
This is for those out there that do not respond to messages or offers for their items.  

You do realize that if someone is contacting you regarding your posted item that it means that they may be interested.   It is only in your best interest to respond to the message.  

Even if you are not happy or interested in their offer or trade just say no thanks.  If you are no longer selling that item for any reason then deactivate the post.  

Now please tell me why when someone posts an item for trade, and I am offering up exactly what they say they are looking for do they then tell me that they are not interested in that as a trade?  When I simply state that I am offering you what you said you would trade for I then get a response back that is telling me that I obviously don't know or have knowledge of firearms.  Well I am sorry but when you ask for a glock 19 Gen 3 that is like new and I respond with a glock 19 Gen 3 new in the box never fired and has 2 extra glock mags, guess what.  THAT'S THE SAME THING!

This is not rocket science and it doesn't hurt to just be polite.

postcontent:
For sale is a high-end pre-charged pneumatic (PCP) .22 caliber air rifle.  This is a beautifully crafted English rifle.  The bluing on the metal is just phenomenal!  The stock is ambidextrous and it's a side-lever action repeater with a 10-shot rotary magazine.  

One of the most unique features of this rifle is the power adjuster.  You can shoot it on high-power and get 30 good shots at 935 fps with JSB Jumbo pellets.  This equates to almost 31 foot-pounds of energy.  If you're shooting closer targets you can turn down the power and easily get 60-70 shots before filling it with air.  The rifle is fantastically accurate.  Check out the target photos.  These 10-shot groups are at 100 YARDS.  Did you think a pellet gun could ever be this accurate a this distance?!?!

If you're not familiar with PCP air rifles this site gives a good description of how they work:
http://www.straightshooters.com/what-are-pcp-air-rifles.html

I have a Hill Mk III hand pump to fill the rifle.  It takes less than 5 minutes to pump it up from my low pressure (125 BAR) back up to my high pressure (180 BAR).  You can read reviews on this pump here:

http://www.pyramydair.com/product-all-reviews/a/Hill_Pump_MK3_Up_to_3300_PSI/3714

I am selling the rifle and pump as a package for $1,200.  This is the cost of the rifle alone if purchased new.

title: For Sale:  Rare GERMAN CG Haenel SCHMEISER Auto Pistol 25 acp NAZI
postcontent:
Offered for sale is a CG Haenel SCHMEISSER Auto Pistol in 25 cal. ACP, manufactured in Suhl during the 1920's before the rise of the NAZI Party, these were the preferred hide-out guns carried by elite Officers of the Wehrmacht and SS, as a backup weapon for their Luger sidearms. Designed by the same man who designed the infamous German MP40 Submachine guns and later refined by Heinrich Vollmer at the Erme Werkes.

This particular gun was made for German use. The later guns made for export around the world had "Made in Germany" stamped on the slide, this one does not, thus proving this was in use during WW2 in Germany.  It is the early First Variant Model 1, and the most sought after by collectors now, as it was for the Wehrmacht & SS in WW2.

These pistols are the smallest, most reliable pocket guns of all the German pistols, that were pressed into service during WW2. Highly concealable, accurate and deadly at close range. Slide it into your vest pocket, and you'll forget you're even carrying. It has a minimal imprint signature when hidden.

This one is an un-refinished gun with a beautiful plum-brown wartime patina in very good+ condition, with a nice bore, excellent grips, original correct magazine, all matching numbers and clear proof marks, and will make a fine investment grade addition to anyone's collection who enjoys German weapons of that era.

Offered @  $395  
(but I'll consider possible trades for the right guns of similar value, or best offers)

Email me through ArmsList reply mail, for additional info or photos.

Cash only for local Columbus, GA sales, but I'm willing to ship FFL to FFL anywhere in the USA, if you assume all transfer/shipping costs. 

I also accept PayPal + 4% for payment too. I'm a VERIFIED PayPal account holder, so you can purchase this item using your Credit/Bank card, even if you don't have a PayPal account. PayPal will send you an invoice, and in a few simple clicks you're done.  Simple, fast, easy and secure!

THANKS FOR LOOKING!
